{{refimprove|date=August 2007}}

'''Navy Occupational Safety & Health''' ('''NAVOSH''') is a [[U.S. Navy]] organization. It is responsible for [[safety]] practices within the Navy.

== Mission ==
NAVOSH provides safety assistance and advice to the [[Chief of Naval Operations|CNO]], CMC, and the Deputy Assistant [[United States Secretary of the Navy|SECNAV]] for Safety with the aim of enhancing the [[war]]-fighting capability of the Navy and [[Marines|Marine Corps]], preserve resources, and improve [[combat readiness]] by preventing mishaps and saving lives.

== External links ==
* [http://safetycenter.navy.mil/training/default.htm NAVOSH and Environmental Training Center]
* [http://www.safetycenter.navy.mil/services/mission.htm Naval Safety Center]
